President Obama has announced his intent to appoint three individuals to key administration posts. Tim Carlson will be appointed as the United States Representative to the Governing Board of the Tahoe Regional Planning Agency. Richard Ginman will be appointed as the Chair of the Government Accountability and Transparency Board. Major General Don Loranger, USAF (Ret) will be appointed as a member of the National Security Education Board. President Obama praised these individuals for their experience and dedication, stating that they will serve the nation well in their new roles.